    <p><strong>The smart buying strategy:</strong> Use 304 for all worktop surfaces and sinks; use 202 for structural frames, legs, racks, and shelving. This hybrid approach gives you food-safe surfaces where it matters while saving 30–35% on the structural components. Most good fabricators in India understand this and will offer "304 top, 202 frame" as standard.</p>

    <h2>2. Stainless Steel Work Tables: The Foundation of Every Kitchen</h2>
    <p>The work table is the most-used piece of steel kitchen equipment in any commercial kitchen. Chefs prep, plate, assemble, and stage food on these tables every single service. A poorly made table that wobbles, rusts, or dents will slow down your kitchen and frustrate your staff daily. Getting this right is non-negotiable.</p>

